 &quot;Thank you Hera.&quot; she said softly. She turned back and sat down once more by the fire. <br>
 Solari managed to rest a bit before those who were sent out to get the information were due back. The pain in her body was subsiding, not that a little pain was going to stop Solari anyway. She thought about what had been discussed with Hera and prayed that Hippolyta was holding out. She was really going to make the Roman that took her suffer. Solari was going to kill him herself, but she thought about it further and decided that he needed to have a dose of his own medicine and therefore, she was going to take him captive, so everyone could relish in a kill.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#993300>(4/21/03 10:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=169>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: tests</span><hr size=1> Alysia growled as she could hear the men shouting. She turned her eyes downward and saw Scythe in a fight with one of their dogs. She yelled, &quot;Scythe, what are you doing!?&quot;<br>
<br>
Scythe growled as it continued fighting.<br>
&quot;It spotted my pack my Queen.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alysia pawed closer and shouted.<br>
&quot;Then kill the darn thing so that we may continue.&quot;<br>
<br>
Scythe growled lowly to the dog and in front of one of the Roman men that had come closer, ripped out the throat of the animal.<br>
<br>
Alysia shouted.<br>
&quot;Mask yourselves!&quot;<br>
<br>
Each white wolf did as they were told and adapted into the shadows becomming unseen to mortal eyes.<br>
<br>
Alysia however was different. She, Arixa and Aeceus pawed closer to the village. Romans had seen them. And if they knew exactly what was going on, they would hurt Hippolyte for it. Aly wouldn't allow that to happen.<br>
<br>
She came as close as she could to the tent where Hippolyte was kept. The Roman who saw the wolves would pay for this. And his blood would soon be brought by the wolf Queen. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
